  ],
  "text": "The LibreOffice document model architecture is built on the following core C++ classes:\n\n1. **SfxObjectShell** (include/sfx2/objsh.hxx:182) - The base document shell class that all document types inherit from. This is the foundation for the Sfx (Staroffice Framework) document management system. It inherits from SfxShell and SotObject.\n\n2. **SwDoc** (sw/inc/doc.hxx:196) - The Writer (word processor) document class. This represents the model of a Writer document and is marked as final. SwDoc is the core data structure for all text document functionality.\n\n3. **ScDocument** (sc/inc/document.hxx:331) - The Calc (spreadsheet) document class. This is the central document object for spreadsheet operations, containing all data and logic for the Calc module.\n\n4. **SdDrawDocument** (sd/inc/drawdoc.hxx:338) - The Impress/Draw document class. This inherits from FmFormModel and manages the presentation and drawing document model, marked as final.\n\n5. **SfxApplication** (include/sfx2/app.hxx:103) - The LibreOffice application framework entry point. This is a singleton class that serves as the top-level application shell, inheriting from SfxShell.\n\nThese classes form a hierarchical architecture where SfxObjectShell serves as the base for all document types (SwDocShell for Writer, ScDocShell for Calc, SdDrawDocShell for Impress/Draw), which in turn manage their respective document models (SwDoc, ScDocument, SdDrawDocument). The SfxApplication singleton coordinates the overall application framework above all document shells."
}

